{0 day11-sys}

Process execution primitives and filesystem utilities. {!Day11_sys.Run} launches
subprocesses via Eio with captured stdout/stderr. {!Day11_sys.Sudo} wraps
commands with privilege escalation for root-owned container artifacts.
{!Day11_sys.Dir_lock} provides dual-layer (in-process Eio mutex + cross-process
POSIX lockf) directory locking. {!Day11_sys.Fork_client} avoids the cost of
forking a large process by delegating to a small helper daemon.
{!Day11_sys.Atomic_swap} implements staging/commit/rollback for atomic directory
replacement. {!Day11_sys.Tree} provides recursive hardlink, copy, and diff-based
cleansing of directory trees. {!Day11_sys.Util} has miscellaneous helpers
(nproc, dir_size).

No domain knowledge — this library provides generic OS-level building
blocks used by every layer above it in the hierarchy.

